<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="732" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                            <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Bigelow</persName></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 405.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-02"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 2, 1866.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatch of the
                                9th of February, No. 268, and I have placed it with pleasure upon
                                the records of the department. It shows that you have compromised no
                                part of the position of this government in your conversation with
                                Mr. Drouyn de Lhuys, and I notice with satisfaction the friendly
                                spirit with which he accepts your explanation. It is hardly
                                necessary to say that the misapprehensions which you have now
                                corrected excited no particular uneasiness here.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>